From: Brian Cain <bcain@quicinc.com>
Date: Thu, 24 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] LinkerWrapper: Exclude libLW from LLVMExports

When ELD is built as LLVM_EXTERNAL_PROJECTS, libLW.so is exported as
SHARED IMPORTED in LLVMExports.cmake.  The per-target builtins sub-build
for hexagon-unknown-none-elf (CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME=Generic) does
find_package(LLVM) which loads these exports, and CMake rejects
SHARED IMPORTED targets on platforms where TARGET_SUPPORTS_SHARED_LIBS
is FALSE ("platform does not support dynamic linking").

Add NO_EXPORT to add_llvm_library(LW ...) so libLW is excluded from the
LLVM export set.  install(TARGETS LW ...) already handles installation
independently.
---
 lib/LinkerWrapper/CMakeLists.txt | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/lib/LinkerWrapper/CMakeLists.txt b/lib/LinkerWrapper/CMakeLists.txt
--- a/lib/LinkerWrapper/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/lib/LinkerWrapper/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -71,6 +71,7 @@
 add_llvm_library(
   LW
   ${SHARED_LIB_SOURCES}
+  NO_EXPORT
   PARTIAL_SOURCES_INTENDED
   DEPENDS
   ${PLUGIN_ELD_DEPENDENCIES}
--
